Need for Speed: The Run runs across America.
Resenya
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of inappropriate neglects of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this is useless if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which The Run is added to the title, aroused high expectations even before its release.
It promised to give new air to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result of what is shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action again without more.
We are also curious to know how the scenes would be inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total computation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, errors cannot be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible failure of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
He introduces you to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to take part in an illegal race across America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
From this it follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to previous series deliveries.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But walking through the desert, the autumnal landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to be buried by an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a required number of opponents (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel), and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes appears the police, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
It's not complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than one might expect (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of the previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big thing, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action is quite suitable for this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true of collisions.
From games of this type you can not expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, with which everything is not in order.
It is typical that when making a very tight overtaking or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
It even ends up completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that when you have an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resets are available for each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is only a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, even resetting does not help, it only helps to learn the given memory stage.
A major disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see two cars going in opposite directions, your opponent goes ahead without problems, but when you arrive, you have to turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, you will always be ahead of the same opponent in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at whatever price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can pamper the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it’s a shame, because even if the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit is taking the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so it doesn’t fit boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is changing cars during races.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline suppliers next to the road, because right there you have to change the car, although in the vast majority of cases you will be enough what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supersports for technical driving, for example, on mountain roads with curves.
In addition to the main narrative thread, a parallel challenge thread also appears, that is, there are races in specific places that you will get to know through the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both the challenges and the stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver has several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community features available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you arrive to the subway tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark along the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the convoy of the metro and takes you ahead without more.
In the editorial we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or whether the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but be prepared because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of some airport spotlights.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Estudiantes de Velvet".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
Twenty choirs of high school and university centers will be presented during the event.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
“The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival.”
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub <0xC4><0x8C>aloun.
