Fujimori hospitalized again for medical examinations
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital on Tuesday to be evaluated for the loss of muscle strength in his legs, his head doctor said.
Fujimori, 72, who serves 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his rule (1990-2000), suffers from various ailments, including cancer of the tongue, which he has operated on four times and is kept under control.
Congressman Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal physician, told Channel N television that Fujimori will be evaluated for three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases to determine the reason for the pain and loss of strength of his lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented that in his opinion Fujimori would be a candidate to obtain the benefit of the pardon for humanitarian reasons, however, he said he does not want it because he is known to be innocent.
He was operated on four times of tongue cancer, has a weight loss of 18 kilograms to which have been added other pathologies such as severe erosive gastritis, pancreatic cyst, kidney stones, hypertension and circulatory problems in the legs, the doctor listed.
Fujimori has served imprisonment since September 2007 in the National Directorate of Special Police Operations.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the deaths of 25 people at the hands of an army annihilation squad that operated clandestinely in the early years of his government.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political ties
An official group, headed by Uruguayan President José Mujica and composed of several ministers and entrepreneurs, will begin a visit to Mexico on Tuesday in order to expand trade between the two nations and address political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican counterpart Felipe Calderón, the highest point of an extensive agenda of meetings with political and commercial authorities and a meeting with the community of Uruguayans living in Mexico, according to the agenda disseminated by the Uruguayan Presidency.
The meeting between the two presidents, in the city of Guadalajara, will be "proper for the exchange of information in all the political affairs between the two nations," the South American presidency said on its website.
According to local media, Mujica would seek to get Calderón to support Uruguay in the incident with France that arose when French President Nicolas Sarkozy included the country on a list of tax havens, at the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
In his speech, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community those countries that remain tax havens, a statement that provoked Uruguay’s rejection and the call for consultation of its ambassador to the European country.
Mexico has chaired the G20 since November, a group made up of the world’s most powerful emerging and developed countries, and has been in force with the South American country since January this year, an agreement to exchange tax information in order to avoid double taxation.
In recent years, the Uruguayan government has tried to speed up the implementation of fiscal exchange agreements in order to get out of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) gray list, made up of countries that have not implemented all the international standards of cooperation in tax matters.
At the trade level, Mexico and Uruguay have a Free Trade Agreement (FTA) in force since 2004 that has increased the exchange of goods between the two nations.
The bigoted plumber passes all three dimensions with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has fought, tirelessly, for 25 years to save Princess Peach from the clutches of the evil Bowser, but never before had he done so in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he will fight for the girl's love in stereoscopic technology.
The title, which comes to stores around the world this month, has been designed from the beginning to take advantage of the features of the Nintendo 3DS portable console, which allows you to play in three dimensions without the need to use glasses.
“Mario is the character who has to say how stereoscopy without glasses should work,” said Omar <0xC3><0x81>lvarez, Nintendo’s specialty press officer in Spain, during the video game’s presentation in Madrid.
<0xC3><0x81>lvarez said "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first Nintendo video game originally designed for that support", as hits such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" were adaptations of existing titles.
Nintendo’s spokesman has argued that, despite being in 3D, “Super Mario 3D Land” is an “accessible” video game that allows you to enjoy a fast and smooth gameplay.
<0xC3><0x81>lvarez has claimed that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: the first part is "simple" to hook up less skilled users.
Once overcome, the most skilled will be able to give a "second turn" to the levels of the game, which this time present greater difficulty.
In addition, users will be able to choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action, but it will be necessary to play in three dimensions in order to be able to overcome the different challenges and "not succumb to optical illusions".
This Super Mario incursion in the three dimensions also involves the return of the character to a portable console, a fact that has not occurred since 2005.
In this video game Nintendo winks at the fans of the saga and repeats the formula of the success of the previous deliveries, consisting in that the mustache plumber will have to roam mined platforms of danger in order to release Princess Peach.
Although the player will find novelties in movements, environments, costumes and enemies and also a "playable" Luigi.
Colom approves Portillo’s extradition to the United States
President <0xC3><0x81>lvaro Colom announced on Tuesday that he gave formality to the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo to answer in the United States for the conspiracy to launder $70 million.
Thus ends the process for Guatemala to respond to the request of the northern country that was demanding Portillo to judge him there.
In a press conference, Colom said his decision was due to the independence of the judiciary and executive powers, taking into account that a court of sentence had already ordered extradition.
He claimed that during his tenure, he "did not put his hands" on court decisions and filed all the extraditions he has known.
In addition to Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín will be extradited for murder and serious injury, and Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Colom's action is an executive procedure after all judicial and constitutional proceedings to prosecute the former president from 2000 to 2004 have been exhausted.
According to decisions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Constitutional Court (CC), Portillo must be extradited once he has resolved his legal situation in Guatemala and his human rights are guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted of the Q120 million defamation in the Ministry of Defense when he was president, which was the process prior to extradition, but the Prosecutor appealed and revived the case.
Trinihove has helped 6,000 young people at risk
The entity was born to prevent the drop in the marginality of untrained boys
The balance sheet of the first 25 years of life of the social support entity Trinijove is important: 6,000 young people at risk of exclusion have been helped to overcome a difficult situation throughout this quarter of a century.
In addition to this, there are hundreds of jobs currently available for this social group.
The anniversary served yesterday to take stock of an event held at the former factory complex of Fabra i Coats attended by more than 300 people.
Trinijove was born in the district of Trinitat Vella in 1986 with the aim of helping young people with little training, without work, with problems of graduation or in a situation of falling into marginality.
Yesterday’s celebration in Sant Andreu concentrated a large number of leaders of entities and institutions that in these 25 years have collaborated with the association.
The varied political representation, in full electoral time, showed the unitary character of the work carried out by Trinijove.
Along with the President of the Generalitat, Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol, attended the event the former Socialist Education Councillor, Ernest Maragall, and the former Mayor and current Ecosocialist Councillor Ricard Gomà.
The large hall of La Fabra i Coats was also attended by the current Social Welfare and Family Councillor, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the general director of the social work of La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa.
Mas said that Trinihove was born in a very difficult time and that today is also, but added that the work done so far "is a good basis".
The president set Trinihove as an example for knowing how to fight against bad circumstances and for giving hope to people in difficulty.
“The crisis is not something new for the entity and for the work it does,” he said.
Evicted an occupied farm where macrofiestas were made
The invaders had seized 11 of the 13 floors of the building, in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants left the farm at noon yesterday without offering resistance.
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare that lived the neighbors of 51 of Balmes Street has come to an end.
Twelve people voluntarily left yesterday noon the property they were illegally occupying, and where they were organizing macrofiestas that were desperate for the neighborhood, by court order and without the need for police intervention.
When the operation ended, the door lock was changed to prevent the situation from repeating.
"From now on there will be access control," the administrator said.
The okupas, who had invaded 11 of the 13 floors of the building -the rest are inhabited-, took all the electrical installation and part of the water, as well as painting the walls and leaving waste of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The first three floors were the scene of crowded parties, lasting up to two days and desperate for tenants.
Next to the building is a nightclub, Balmes 51, which has also been damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that since the building was occupied the business has fallen by 80%.
The owner of the club points out that the invaders of the estate were unfair competition, as they sold the cups for three euros, while in the club they are worth 10.
In addition, the owner of the leisure room had to respond to neighboring complaints about noise, while, according to the point, the discomfort is not caused by the customers of the disco, but the inhabitants of the occupied house and, above all, the attendees to the parties that were organized there, which had increased their frequency and intensity in the last few weeks, according to the vecino.
The head of the club explained that the inconveniences were so great that he even reached an agreement with the owner of the property and for nine months he "forgave" the rent.
The City Guard also confirmed that in recent weeks it had received more complaints from neighbors about the situation.
The president of the municipal group of the PP in the city, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had claimed last week "immediately evicting the property to end the problems of coexistence and civility that produce the neighbors, as well as the degradation of the area".
The popular leader explained that before the summer there was only one floor of the building occupied, but over the last few months the okupas had been entering all the floors of the building and almost all the floors, and that in some even thefts have occurred.
In this sense, he added, "it is necessary to end impunity and be convincing against the incivism that has been generated on the farm".
Also yesterday, the Mossos evicted a building in Nou Barris.
At 3.30 p.m., police rushed to 35 rue de Mont-ral, after receiving a call from a neighbor who had observed four people accessing the building.
All four were arrested at the time.
The park or the mountain?
Architects agree on the opportunity of the call beyond controversy about fees
The municipal competition on the 16 doors reopens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the already extinct Metropolitan Corporation of Barcelona (CMB), this Administration printed a few promotional banners for Collserola.
The booklet defined the mountain as the great metropolitan Barcelona park.
Moreover, it was accompanied by a comparison, in figures, with New York City’s Central Park.
With the death of the CMB, in 1987, the park was again located, in the imagination of many, as the upper limit of Barcelona, being the Catalan capital of the few that do not orient on the north-south axis but up (mountain) -down (sea).
The classification of Collserola as a natural park is reflected in this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with the wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
It was in these until, in September, the city called a mega competition consisting of 16 contests for so many other gates to Collserola.
A door refers to the idea of park, without a doubt.
Either that or someone wants to put doors in the field.
The question arises by itself: Collserola, park or mountain?
The competition, both for its purely organizational aspect and for what it means to reflect on the city, is the topic of conversation among all Barcelona architects.
It’s almost a recurring theme when two members of this ancient caste of elect recognize each other in an elevator.
And this fact justifies one of the few coincidences between what three Barcelona architects, and university professors, have said.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel M<0xC3><0xB2>dol and Marta Bayona: the competition is timely.
For Roldán, after approaching the coastal front "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain front", since the speech of Ildefons Cerdà, that of the green apples, has not taken place.
"We can start from the premise that the most extensive park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things, due to its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex,” says the architect for whom the title of “Colserola’s gates” encloses a “lexical trap”: one should not think of them “as access to a park, but the delimitation of areas where action must be taken”.
M<0xC3><0xB2>dol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the urban world, qualifies the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers".
Dangers derived from the "uncertainty that it is today to project public space" after the experience experienced in the 80s and that had in the area of the Forum "swan's song".
The first fear is the very delimitation of borders on where it can be built.
“Limiting something is fixing the next step,” that is, overstepping it.
"You have to think about new urban planning instruments, because the current ones [in reference to the Metropolitan General Plan (PGM)] can lead to real disasters."
More closely to the question, M<0xC3><0xB2>dol thinks that, by simplifying, the Vallesan side of Collserola "can be understood as a park, that of Barcelona, not", by a merely topographic issue.
M<0xC3><0xB2>dol recalls that there is already a work done by the Patronat de Collserola that "should not fall into a broken bag", although he appreciates the opportunity that the city council offers his guild to intervene in this project "from the first moment".
And even more, he understands that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the lifeline that allows architects to enter the debate, but "doubts" about whether it is this technical profile that should lead the multidisciplinary teams ("all a success", he points out) that have had to create: "Architects should only be a tool".
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gives title to this piece is complex, because in the foundations of the contest there is a lack of a global vision of Collserola: "16 cross competitions have been convened -he says- in the mountain-sea direction, but there is no longitudinal reading, which sees and understands the area as a whole".
This causes, at least in your case, that you have chosen to participate in the 16 contests.
Otherwise, a project for one of the doors can collide in program and definition with that of the next door architect.
In its view, yes, the City Council should ensure that the strip immediately above the Dalt Round should provide, in its entirety, an area of equipment that would effect a smooth transition between the city and the greenery.
Casino forgives Jonas Larrazábal and will be free
After 72 days of rooting, the legal representative of Casino Red granted forgiveness to the brother of the mayor of Monterrey of the process that followed him for alleged blackmail
After being held for 72 days, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the legal representative of Casino Red granted him forgiveness before the Second District Criminal Court, which follows a blackmail trial against the mayor’s brother.
After the attack on Casino Royale, Red Casino owner Sergio Gil García made public a series of photographs and videos in which Manuel Jonas allegedly demanded that he pay an economic fee for the regiomontano city council to allow the clandestine operation of the bookmaker.
