The Microcredit Summit stands not only as a forum for debate, but also as the platform from which to promote “two basic goals”.
Thus, His Majesty explained that the aim is for 175 million poor families to have access to these financial services by the end of 2015 and for 100 million of those households to get out of the poverty line in which they are immersed.
