Jiménez said that microcredit is “a serious and rigorous policy dedicated to eradicating poverty”, and now “more than ever” governments in developed countries must work under solidarity criteria and not let it be a victim of cuts.
For Spain, microcredit is "one of the main lines of development cooperation".
